# codealpha_tasks
Student Management System (C)
Project Overview

Student Management System is a simple menu-driven application developed in C language to manage student records. The project performs basic student operations and stores data permanently using file handling.
This project was created to practice fundamental C programming concepts including structures, functions, file handling, and record management.

->Features
.Add Student Record
.Delete Student Record
.Update Student Record
.Search Student Record
.Display All Student Records
.Permanent Data Storage using File Handling

->Menu Driven Interface
1.Concepts Used
2.C Programming
3.Structures (struct)
4.Functions
5.File Handling (fopen, fprintf, fscanf)

->Switch Case
.Conditional Statements
.Record Management
.Project Structure
student_management/
│
├── main.c
├── student.txt
└── README.md

->How It Works
1.User selects an operation from the menu.
2.Student details are entered and stored in student.txt.
3.Records can be searched using Roll Number.
4.Existing records can be updated or deleted.
5.Display option shows all available student records.
6.File Storage
student.txt

This file stores:
Roll Number
Student Name

Data remains saved even after closing the program.

